history.content:
They work the same way in that you need to be able to enroll in both the lecture and the discussion. They work differently in that seats are not reserved for anyone; this means that no extra seats are going to magically be released. Enough people must drop from both the lecture and your discussion section for you to enroll.

We might hypothesize that a handful of students are enrolled in the summer class in case they need to repeat it from this semester. If they do well and drop the summer class, you may be in luck. Impossible to know without more information.
